; LINEAR analogue of recursive_to_downstream (the A4 ready_after seam test).
; A LINEAR transitive-closure recursion feeding a HIGHER differential
; stratum consumer, so net-removal AND net-addition frontiers cross the
; producer -> consumer seam.
;
; The recursion is LINEAR: the recursive rule has EXACTLY ONE same-SCC body
; atom (tc), the other (edge) is a lower stratum. This matters: the
; linearity gate at lib/ControlFlow/Build/Stratum.cpp ~1010 routes a rule
; with >=2 same-SCC sides (as in recursive_to_downstream's tc(From,X),
; tc(X,To)) to the single-pass fallback, which would make this fixture
; inert. The linear shape keeps tc on the claim-round D/R/I path this
; fixture is meant to exercise.
;
; Downstream consumer: marked(X) := tc reachable from a watched node AND
; watch(X); flagged(X) := marked(X) AND watch(X). A broken BUILDFRONTIERS
; wiring (recursive-stratum outDel/outAdd not populated, or consumed with
; the wrong sign) changes flagged's final membership WITHOUT tripping any
; single-stratum counter assert -- a cross-stratum WIRING bug -- so this
; needs an END-STATE oracle comparison.
;
; The batches exercise all three seam directions: a removal retracting
; downstream rows (drain), an addition re-creating them (fill), and an
; OVERDELETE-then-REDERIVE survivor whose downstream row must NOT flap
; (the discriminator for the T1 frontier-ordering fix).
#message add_edge(u64 From, u64 To) @differential.
#message watch(u64 X) @differential.

#local tc(From, To).
#local edge(From, To).
#local marked(X).
#local flagged(X).

edge(From, To) : add_edge(From, To).

tc(From, To) : edge(From, To).
tc(From, To) : tc(From, X), edge(X, To).

marked(X) : tc(W, X), watch(W).
flagged(X) : marked(X), watch(X).

#query flagged_out(free u64 X).
flagged_out(X) : flagged(X).
